The paper deals with steganography detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks also suggests a possible fit with machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the experiments conducted on large-scale databases and the use of feature-based methods suggest a possible fit with information retrieval (cs.IR).
